    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound E92 M3 featuring the legendary S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and a cross-bank exhaust manifold to deliver linear power up to its 8,400 RPM redline. The 6-speed longitudinal manual transmission offers precise shift gates, paired with the Variable M Differential Lock for optimal torque vectoring. Recent preventative maintenance includes updated rod bearings and throttle actuators, ensuring the VANOS system and valvetrain remain within factory tolerances. The chassis retains its structural rigidity with no subframe fatigue, and the Electronic Damper Control (EDC) provides adjustable damping rates for both track-focused stiffness and street compliance. Finished with staggered 19-inch forged alloys and Michelin Pilot Sport rubber, this specimen represents a well-maintained example of BMW's final naturally aspirated M-car.",
